Sales Electrical Engineer Job (Electrical Manufacturing) Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Manufacturing
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting for a Multinational company that has been active in the Electrical Manufacturing Sector. Our client is seeking a professional, with a background in electrical engineering, to fill the job of Electrical Engineer, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. Our client has become a worldwide leader in their industry segment and delivers value to its clients by betting on constant business development, advertising excellence and high-quality human resources. The winning candidate will experience a dynamic, stimulating and international environment, allowing them to grow professionally. The company offers good prospects for career progression.
Key job responsibilities will include:
To help in analysis and interpretation of bid documents
Be in charge of electrical project management
Be in charge of cost estimations in proposals, technical offers and specifications
Maintain relationship with customers and suppliers
Performing sales activity assigned to ensure in achieving an optimum level of business.
Responsible for formulating and implementing short terms and mid terms Sales Strategy. Accountable for the achievements of Sales volume targets and growth within specific assignment
Responsible for the evaluations and approval of sales proposal prior to proposal release.  Evaluations must cover legal and commercial aspect
Responsible for establishing customer or prospect interface and retaining valuable clients for future business
Responsible for all required reporting to be available in timely manner
Incumbent should develop Sales Strategy with Sales Manager
Ensure that Commercial, legal and technical aspects are being done properly to minimized company risk and maximized profit.
Requirements:
Bachelor in Electrical Engineering Degree
2 – 3 years experiences in electrical projects
Strong networking in government/private companies
Cost Estimation
Excellent team work and organizational skills
Excellent English communication skills, both written and verbal.
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.